SUMMARY OF QUANTITIES
THE CONTRACTOR SHALL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR SUBMITTING THE FDOT STANDARD PLAN INDICES WHICH WILL BE USED FOR
TEMPORARY TRAFFIC CONTROL. TEMPORARY TRAFFIC CONTROL WHICH IS NOT COVERED WITHIN THE FDOT STANDARD PLANS INDICES
WILL REQUIRE A DETAILED TEMPORARY TRAFFIC CONTROL PLAN. THE DETAILED TEMPORARY TRAFFIC CONTROL PLAN SHALL BE
SIGNED & SEALED BY A FLORIDA PROFESSIONAL ENGINEER WHICH DEFINES THE PROPOSED TRAFFIC PATTERNS FOR ALL PHASES OF
CONSTRUCTION. PROVISIONS FOR TEMPORARY DRAINAGE AS WELL AS MAINTAINING ACCESS TO ALL PROPERTIES SHALL BE INCLUDED
AND DEFINED WITHIN THE PLAN.  THE COST OF THIS ITEM SHALL INCLUDE ALL LABOR, MATERIAL AND AND TEMPORARY TRAFFIC
CONTROL EQUIPMENT NECESSARY TO IMPLEMENT AND MAINTAIN THE APPROVED TEMPORARY TRAFFIC CONTROL PLAN.
THIS PAY ITEM ALSO INCLUDES LITTER REMOVAL AND DISPOSAL AND MOWING AS REQUIRED PER SECTION 107 OF THE JULY 2022
STANDARD SPECIFICATIONS FOR ROAD AND BRIDGE CONSTRUCTION.
INCLUDES THE COST OF ALL LABOR AND EQUIPMENT NECESSARY TO REMOVE AND DISPOSE OF EXISTING CONCRETE PAVEMENT AND
CURBING. REFER TO MARION COUNTY SPECIFICATIONS FOR ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS.
EXCAVATION AND EMBANKMENT QUANTITIES ARE LUMP SUM ITEMS AND INCLUDE ALL LABOR AND MATERIAL NECESSARY TO CONSTRUCT
THE PROJECT.  THERE WILL BE NO VOLUMETRIC ADJUSTMENT FACTORS USED.
MARION COUNTY MAY CONSIDER THE USE OF ALTERNATIVE MATERIAL (INSTEAD OF RCP) BASED ON VALUE ENGINEERING PROPOSALS.
